WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:26.550 align:middle line:90%


00:00:26.550 --> 00:00:29.364 align:middle line:84%
>>One of the psychiatrists
on the program

00:00:29.364 --> 00:00:31.030 align:middle line:84%
sitting here with me,
I know that you'll

00:00:31.030 --> 00:00:35.370 align:middle line:84%
appreciate the great power,
or whole body experience,

00:00:35.370 --> 00:00:37.060 align:middle line:84%
such as a re-stimulating
experience

00:00:37.060 --> 00:00:40.330 align:middle line:84%
that I had this evening when
I had dinner at the V & T

00:00:40.330 --> 00:00:44.160 align:middle line:84%
Pizzeria across the street--
the place where I ate hundreds

00:00:44.160 --> 00:00:46.600 align:middle line:84%
of meals when I was a
graduate student at Columbia

00:00:46.600 --> 00:00:49.150 align:middle line:84%
University which is also
just across the street.

00:00:49.150 --> 00:00:52.579 align:middle line:90%


00:00:52.579 --> 00:00:54.870 align:middle line:84%
I wanted to know what I should
talk about this evening.

00:00:54.870 --> 00:00:58.720 align:middle line:84%
And Robin said, well, just
talk about your spiritual path.

00:00:58.720 --> 00:01:01.992 align:middle line:84%
So that's a path
that started in 1954.

00:01:01.992 --> 00:01:04.599 align:middle line:84%
I was a graduate
student in physics

00:01:04.599 --> 00:01:09.160 align:middle line:84%
with some of the toughest task
masters around-- TD Lee and CS

00:01:09.160 --> 00:01:11.810 align:middle line:84%
Wu and a bunch of other very
difficult and inscrutable

00:01:11.810 --> 00:01:15.030 align:middle line:84%
people that I worked
for for many years.

00:01:15.030 --> 00:01:17.630 align:middle line:84%
And somehow over the
ensuing 45 years,

00:01:17.630 --> 00:01:22.260 align:middle line:84%
I'm here today to describe
my path from atomic physicist

00:01:22.260 --> 00:01:23.950 align:middle line:84%
to the mashed potato
you see today.

00:01:23.950 --> 00:01:27.320 align:middle line:90%


00:01:27.320 --> 00:01:30.000 align:middle line:84%
Now I had a chance to
do many different things

00:01:30.000 --> 00:01:31.360 align:middle line:90%
during that career.

00:01:31.360 --> 00:01:34.510 align:middle line:84%
I spent half of my time
working on the development

00:01:34.510 --> 00:01:37.810 align:middle line:84%
of the laser, which came out
of my atomic spectroscopy

00:01:37.810 --> 00:01:43.300 align:middle line:84%
at Columbia and half of my time
doing ESP research at Stanford

00:01:43.300 --> 00:01:47.220 align:middle line:84%
Research Institute, where we had
the interesting task of trying

00:01:47.220 --> 00:01:52.610 align:middle line:84%
to increase the reliability and
accuracy of psychic functioning

00:01:52.610 --> 00:01:55.860 align:middle line:84%
and learning to put
government scientists and army

00:01:55.860 --> 00:01:58.640 align:middle line:84%
intelligence officers
in touch with apart

00:01:58.640 --> 00:02:01.020 align:middle line:90%
of themselves that's psychic.

00:02:01.020 --> 00:02:04.580 align:middle line:84%
What I learned in my last
job, I was putting lasers

00:02:04.580 --> 00:02:06.030 align:middle line:90%
on airplanes at Lockheed.

00:02:06.030 --> 00:02:07.930 align:middle line:90%
I was in aerospace.

00:02:07.930 --> 00:02:10.160 align:middle line:84%
And all of this I
discovered, my whole career

00:02:10.160 --> 00:02:13.860 align:middle line:84%
has been in remote sensing,
sometimes with ESP, sometimes

00:02:13.860 --> 00:02:16.510 align:middle line:84%
with lasers, but
always trying to see

00:02:16.510 --> 00:02:19.270 align:middle line:90%
what nobody had seen before.

00:02:19.270 --> 00:02:22.860 align:middle line:84%
And in listening to
the discussion tonight,

00:02:22.860 --> 00:02:25.110 align:middle line:84%
it reminds me of
one of the things

00:02:25.110 --> 00:02:27.220 align:middle line:90%
that I noticed in aerospace.

00:02:27.220 --> 00:02:30.750 align:middle line:84%
If you're about to put a
sensor on a satellite that's

00:02:30.750 --> 00:02:33.880 align:middle line:84%
getting launched and
everybody at the table agrees,

00:02:33.880 --> 00:02:37.780 align:middle line:84%
it means you've probably
overlooked something.

00:02:37.780 --> 00:02:40.970 align:middle line:84%
So I'm going to have to be the
person who doesn't entirely

00:02:40.970 --> 00:02:44.820 align:middle line:90%
agree with what we see today.

00:02:44.820 --> 00:02:49.560 align:middle line:84%
In a book that I wrote recently,
called "Miracles of Mind,"

00:02:49.560 --> 00:02:51.850 align:middle line:84%
I was talking about
what we know about

00:02:51.850 --> 00:02:55.620 align:middle line:84%
parapsychology, ESP research,
what we know about physics.

00:02:55.620 --> 00:02:58.445 align:middle line:84%
And I had a wonderful
quote from Stephen Hawking

00:02:58.445 --> 00:03:01.360 align:middle line:84%
that he wrote in
1985, in which he

00:03:01.360 --> 00:03:03.470 align:middle line:84%
said, "by the end
of this decade,

00:03:03.470 --> 00:03:05.420 align:middle line:84%
we will understand
everything there is

00:03:05.420 --> 00:03:07.960 align:middle line:90%
to know about modern physics."

00:03:07.960 --> 00:03:09.660 align:middle line:84%
Now I had the advantage
of writing this

00:03:09.660 --> 00:03:12.360 align:middle line:90%
10 years later in 1995.

00:03:12.360 --> 00:03:14.650 align:middle line:84%
And I sort of
unceremoniously said

00:03:14.650 --> 00:03:18.060 align:middle line:84%
that Stephen better turn the
crank pretty fast because, I

00:03:18.060 --> 00:03:21.100 align:middle line:84%
mean, enormous number of things
on the horizon that were not

00:03:21.100 --> 00:03:24.260 align:middle line:84%
understood and very
unlikely to be understood

00:03:24.260 --> 00:03:27.000 align:middle line:90%
in the next 5, 10, 20 years.

00:03:27.000 --> 00:03:29.300 align:middle line:90%
And indeed, they have not been.

00:03:29.300 --> 00:03:34.250 align:middle line:84%
With regard to understanding the
nature of the world we live in,

00:03:34.250 --> 00:03:36.230 align:middle line:84%
great progress has
obviously been made.

00:03:36.230 --> 00:03:41.260 align:middle line:84%
We can explain with great detail
how the billiard balls move

00:03:41.260 --> 00:03:43.240 align:middle line:90%
on the surface of the table.

00:03:43.240 --> 00:03:46.780 align:middle line:84%
And even with the uncertainty
in quantum physics,

00:03:46.780 --> 00:03:50.590 align:middle line:84%
we can calculate, to at
least eight decimal figures,

00:03:50.590 --> 00:03:53.260 align:middle line:84%
the wavelength of
an atomic transition

00:03:53.260 --> 00:03:56.830 align:middle line:84%
by subtracting the energy
levels in the published tables.

00:03:56.830 --> 00:04:00.300 align:middle line:84%
So atomic physics
works extremely well.

00:04:00.300 --> 00:04:03.720 align:middle line:84%
Maxwell's equations
work excellently.

00:04:03.720 --> 00:04:06.980 align:middle line:84%
But there are things that
come unraveled at the edge

00:04:06.980 --> 00:04:11.060 align:middle line:84%
of the field, little
threads that you

00:04:11.060 --> 00:04:14.730 align:middle line:84%
tug and notice that things
keep coming unraveled.

00:04:14.730 --> 00:04:17.990 align:middle line:84%
One of those in physics
is called "superposition"

00:04:17.990 --> 00:04:20.709 align:middle line:90%
that was alluded to earlier.

00:04:20.709 --> 00:04:23.390 align:middle line:84%
Superposition is
this nasty business

00:04:23.390 --> 00:04:25.220 align:middle line:84%
where you have the
cat in the box that's

00:04:25.220 --> 00:04:27.470 align:middle line:90%
neither alive nor dead.

00:04:27.470 --> 00:04:30.780 align:middle line:84%
It also pertains to the
even nastier problem

00:04:30.780 --> 00:04:33.520 align:middle line:84%
for people in
optics, who observe

00:04:33.520 --> 00:04:37.100 align:middle line:84%
that when you send photons
through a pair of slits,

00:04:37.100 --> 00:04:40.460 align:middle line:84%
even though there's only
one photon in the apparatus

00:04:40.460 --> 00:04:44.240 align:middle line:84%
at a time, you still
observe interference.

00:04:44.240 --> 00:04:45.930 align:middle line:90%
And it's not limited to photons.

00:04:45.930 --> 00:04:50.230 align:middle line:84%
It's limited to really big
things, like buckyballs.

00:04:50.230 --> 00:04:54.400 align:middle line:84%
A buckyball is 60 carbon
atoms arranged the size

00:04:54.400 --> 00:04:58.250 align:middle line:84%
of a soccer ball or in the
configuration of a soccer ball.

00:04:58.250 --> 00:05:00.600 align:middle line:84%
John Clauser, who
was the first person

00:05:00.600 --> 00:05:03.620 align:middle line:84%
to demonstrate
nonlocality, said recently,

00:05:03.620 --> 00:05:08.040 align:middle line:84%
"it looks like you can't keep
anything in a box anymore."

00:05:08.040 --> 00:05:11.590 align:middle line:84%
That is, things that appear to
be separated from one another,

00:05:11.590 --> 00:05:15.320 align:middle line:84%
even in physical reality
appear to interact.

00:05:15.320 --> 00:05:18.020 align:middle line:84%
Henry Stapp, who is a
distinguished physicist

00:05:18.020 --> 00:05:21.690 align:middle line:84%
at the University of
California in Berkeley said,

00:05:21.690 --> 00:05:26.150 align:middle line:84%
"possibly the most important
discovery in all of science,

00:05:26.150 --> 00:05:30.200 align:middle line:84%
in the history of science, is
the discovery of nonlocality."

00:05:30.200 --> 00:05:33.345 align:middle line:84%
Nonlocality was this awful
thing that Einstein, Podolsky,

00:05:33.345 --> 00:05:37.930 align:middle line:84%
and Rosen postulated
in 1935, saying

00:05:37.930 --> 00:05:40.620 align:middle line:84%
that, "even photons traveling
away from each other

00:05:40.620 --> 00:05:44.810 align:middle line:84%
at the speed of light are still
in contact with one another.

00:05:44.810 --> 00:05:47.520 align:middle line:84%
So that if you polarize
one, you notice

00:05:47.520 --> 00:05:50.840 align:middle line:84%
a change in the
polarization of the other."

00:05:50.840 --> 00:05:54.790 align:middle line:84%
Einstein correctly
predicted that this

00:05:54.790 --> 00:05:57.360 align:middle line:84%
is what was predicted
by quantum mechanics.

00:05:57.360 --> 00:06:03.020 align:middle line:84%
He said, therefore, since it
violated special relativity,

00:06:03.020 --> 00:06:05.150 align:middle line:84%
quantum mechanics
couldn't be right.

00:06:05.150 --> 00:06:07.270 align:middle line:84%
However, there have
now been a multitude

00:06:07.270 --> 00:06:11.520 align:middle line:84%
of experiments showing that
these twin photons do indeed

00:06:11.520 --> 00:06:12.950 align:middle line:90%
remain connected.

00:06:12.950 --> 00:06:14.730 align:middle line:84%
And in fact, this
has now been shown

00:06:14.730 --> 00:06:16.720 align:middle line:90%
over many, many kilometers.

00:06:16.720 --> 00:06:19.660 align:middle line:84%
So the idea of this
nonlocal connection

00:06:19.660 --> 00:06:22.690 align:middle line:84%
is not a metaphysical
proposition.

00:06:22.690 --> 00:06:24.740 align:middle line:84%
Of course, Buddha
in his writings,

00:06:24.740 --> 00:06:28.730 align:middle line:84%
said in many different ways
that separation is an illusion.

00:06:28.730 --> 00:06:31.070 align:middle line:84%
That is to say, that
there is only one of us

00:06:31.070 --> 00:06:32.817 align:middle line:90%
here in consciousness.

00:06:32.817 --> 00:06:34.275 align:middle line:84%
And that's why
we're compassionate.

00:06:34.275 --> 00:06:37.950 align:middle line:84%
We're compassionate because
there is in fact only one of us

00:06:37.950 --> 00:06:39.060 align:middle line:90%
here.

00:06:39.060 --> 00:06:42.930 align:middle line:84%
But when Clauser and
Freedman, or Aspect, or Gisin,

00:06:42.930 --> 00:06:45.650 align:middle line:84%
or the distinguished
physicists around the world

00:06:45.650 --> 00:06:49.610 align:middle line:84%
are looking at the nonlocal
connection between particles,

00:06:49.610 --> 00:06:53.430 align:middle line:84%
they're not thinking about ESP,
metaphysics, or consciousness.

00:06:53.430 --> 00:06:55.830 align:middle line:84%
They're thinking about this
very interesting connection

00:06:55.830 --> 00:06:58.950 align:middle line:84%
that they observe in
the physical universe.

00:06:58.950 --> 00:07:01.690 align:middle line:84%
So it's one of the
interesting things

00:07:01.690 --> 00:07:04.540 align:middle line:84%
that's predicted by
quantum theory, observed

00:07:04.540 --> 00:07:05.570 align:middle line:90%
in the laboratory.

00:07:05.570 --> 00:07:07.370 align:middle line:90%
And that's the good news.

00:07:07.370 --> 00:07:11.270 align:middle line:84%
We don't yet have a description
of the space/time in which we

00:07:11.270 --> 00:07:15.120 align:middle line:84%
live that describes the
nature of the metric

00:07:15.120 --> 00:07:18.410 align:middle line:90%
that would give us nonlocality.

00:07:18.410 --> 00:07:22.070 align:middle line:84%
In my other career path, we
do have some interesting data

00:07:22.070 --> 00:07:27.690 align:middle line:84%
that bears on this that is only
beginning to become described

00:07:27.690 --> 00:07:29.830 align:middle line:90%
sensibly by modern physics.

00:07:29.830 --> 00:07:33.320 align:middle line:84%
And that is the data for
extrasensory perception.

00:07:33.320 --> 00:07:36.720 align:middle line:84%
We know a few things without
a shadow of the doubt.

00:07:36.720 --> 00:07:40.660 align:middle line:84%
We know that it's possible
to sit in the laboratory,

00:07:40.660 --> 00:07:43.300 align:middle line:84%
close your eyes,
and quiet your mind,

00:07:43.300 --> 00:07:46.670 align:middle line:84%
and describe with
surprising accuracy what's

00:07:46.670 --> 00:07:49.850 align:middle line:84%
going on in distant
parts of the world.

00:07:49.850 --> 00:07:53.710 align:middle line:84%
We know that a person can
hold a thought in his mind

00:07:53.710 --> 00:07:56.600 align:middle line:84%
and that thought can
be accurately described

00:07:56.600 --> 00:07:59.340 align:middle line:84%
by another person,
even though there

00:07:59.340 --> 00:08:04.960 align:middle line:84%
is no physical, material object
corresponding to that thought.

00:08:04.960 --> 00:08:08.777 align:middle line:84%
Even more astonishing is
that we know-- probably

00:08:08.777 --> 00:08:10.610 align:middle line:84%
the most interesting
thing I could tell you,

00:08:10.610 --> 00:08:12.193 align:middle line:84%
if you don't hear
anything that I say,

00:08:12.193 --> 00:08:14.830 align:middle line:84%
if you don't come tomorrow-- the
most interesting thing I could

00:08:14.830 --> 00:08:20.290 align:middle line:84%
tell you is that it is no
more difficult to describe

00:08:20.290 --> 00:08:23.140 align:middle line:84%
and experience something
that's going to happen

00:08:23.140 --> 00:08:26.470 align:middle line:84%
in your future-- in your
near future-- that's no more

00:08:26.470 --> 00:08:30.340 align:middle line:84%
difficult than to describe
a picture that's face down

00:08:30.340 --> 00:08:32.570 align:middle line:84%
on the table and
hidden from view.

00:08:32.570 --> 00:08:36.200 align:middle line:84%
That is, our ability
to know the future

00:08:36.200 --> 00:08:40.590 align:middle line:84%
can be made as accurate
and reliable as our ability

00:08:40.590 --> 00:08:42.900 align:middle line:90%
to describe the hidden present.

00:08:42.900 --> 00:08:46.850 align:middle line:84%
What that says is not that
there's some magic afoot

00:08:46.850 --> 00:08:49.170 align:middle line:84%
but rather that we
profoundly misunderstand

00:08:49.170 --> 00:08:51.350 align:middle line:84%
the nature of the
causality that,

00:08:51.350 --> 00:08:53.680 align:middle line:84%
in fact, underlies
the organizing

00:08:53.680 --> 00:08:55.810 align:middle line:90%
principles of the universe.

00:08:55.810 --> 00:08:57.930 align:middle line:84%
There's something fundamentally
with our knowledge

00:08:57.930 --> 00:08:59.470 align:middle line:90%
of causality.

00:08:59.470 --> 00:09:04.080 align:middle line:84%
And modern physics has yet
to say the very first word

00:09:04.080 --> 00:09:07.180 align:middle line:84%
about how it is that we
can sit in the laboratory,

00:09:07.180 --> 00:09:09.800 align:middle line:84%
as we did for 20
years, and describe

00:09:09.800 --> 00:09:13.360 align:middle line:84%
what's going on in China,
Soviet Union, Iran hostages.

00:09:13.360 --> 00:09:14.310 align:middle line:90%


00:09:14.310 --> 00:09:15.475 align:middle line:90%
That experiment worked.

00:09:15.475 --> 00:09:18.640 align:middle line:84%
That is, we published in the
proceedings of the Engineering

00:09:18.640 --> 00:09:21.960 align:middle line:84%
Society, Nature Magazine,
Academy of Sciences,

00:09:21.960 --> 00:09:22.700 align:middle line:90%
and so forth.

00:09:22.700 --> 00:09:26.380 align:middle line:84%
That is, the ESP side of
this is not metaphysics.

00:09:26.380 --> 00:09:32.070 align:middle line:84%
We had very tough contract
monitors and NASA, CIA,

00:09:32.070 --> 00:09:35.390 align:middle line:84%
the army-- none of whom
suffer fools gladly.

00:09:35.390 --> 00:09:37.240 align:middle line:84%
And if any of you
have ever tried

00:09:37.240 --> 00:09:39.360 align:middle line:84%
to get government
research money,

00:09:39.360 --> 00:09:42.890 align:middle line:84%
you'll appreciate that the
most paranormal part of this

00:09:42.890 --> 00:09:47.570 align:middle line:84%
is that we had continued support
for ESP research for 23 years.

00:09:47.570 --> 00:09:49.370 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:09:49.370 --> 00:09:54.000 align:middle line:84%
So we must have been
doing something right.

00:09:54.000 --> 00:09:58.670 align:middle line:84%
Now what I discovered, it's as
though I had a spiritual path.

00:09:58.670 --> 00:10:03.030 align:middle line:84%
That is, what I'm telling you
is that somehow I started out

00:10:03.030 --> 00:10:06.690 align:middle line:84%
as a research physicist
and had the opportunity,

00:10:06.690 --> 00:10:09.910 align:middle line:84%
through my career, to
metamorphise from a research

00:10:09.910 --> 00:10:14.170 align:middle line:84%
physicist to a psychic
spy for the CIA.

00:10:14.170 --> 00:10:17.320 align:middle line:84%
And through that path,
I had an opportunity

00:10:17.320 --> 00:10:21.630 align:middle line:84%
to discover that there are
many expansive experiences

00:10:21.630 --> 00:10:23.330 align:middle line:90%
available to us.

00:10:23.330 --> 00:10:26.280 align:middle line:84%
The principle of those
is that the observation

00:10:26.280 --> 00:10:29.500 align:middle line:84%
that there is more
going on than simply

00:10:29.500 --> 00:10:31.650 align:middle line:90%
residing in the physical body.

00:10:31.650 --> 00:10:35.980 align:middle line:84%
That is, we are capable
of expanded awareness

00:10:35.980 --> 00:10:39.540 align:middle line:84%
that allows us to
inflow information

00:10:39.540 --> 00:10:43.940 align:middle line:84%
from distant locations
that is quite verifiable.

00:10:43.940 --> 00:10:45.820 align:middle line:90%
And often surprisingly accurate.

00:10:45.820 --> 00:10:49.910 align:middle line:84%
We can inflow that
information and the distance

00:10:49.910 --> 00:10:51.180 align:middle line:90%
doesn't matter.

00:10:51.180 --> 00:10:55.710 align:middle line:84%
We can also outflow
our healing intention.

00:10:55.710 --> 00:10:59.290 align:middle line:84%
We can sit in a laboratory
if we're trained as a healer

00:10:59.290 --> 00:11:02.455 align:middle line:84%
and affect the physiology
and the physical outcome

00:11:02.455 --> 00:11:04.680 align:middle line:90%
of people who are very sick.

00:11:04.680 --> 00:11:09.110 align:middle line:84%
And that research has been
done in several laboratories,

00:11:09.110 --> 00:11:11.250 align:middle line:84%
including California
Pacific Medical

00:11:11.250 --> 00:11:13.960 align:middle line:84%
Center, where a
recent experiment was

00:11:13.960 --> 00:11:17.770 align:middle line:90%
done with 60 AIDS patients.

00:11:17.770 --> 00:11:20.310 align:middle line:84%
30 of them received
healing prayers.

00:11:20.310 --> 00:11:23.880 align:middle line:84%
The other 30 were controls
in a double blind study.

00:11:23.880 --> 00:11:27.090 align:middle line:84%
So everybody wished that they
were prayed for, of course,

00:11:27.090 --> 00:11:29.280 align:middle line:90%
but only 30 actually were.

00:11:29.280 --> 00:11:33.110 align:middle line:84%
And those 30 had
significantly improved

00:11:33.110 --> 00:11:36.330 align:middle line:84%
outcomes-- fewer opportunistic
illnesses, fewer trips

00:11:36.330 --> 00:11:38.570 align:middle line:90%
to the hospital, and so forth.

00:11:38.570 --> 00:11:43.480 align:middle line:84%
And there are now four large
clinical studies published

00:11:43.480 --> 00:11:46.170 align:middle line:90%
in mainline medical magazines.

00:11:46.170 --> 00:11:51.060 align:middle line:84%
And in a certain sense, in
the same way that experiments

00:11:51.060 --> 00:11:56.040 align:middle line:84%
in nonlocality are the hot
issue in modern physics,

00:11:56.040 --> 00:11:59.510 align:middle line:84%
experiments in distant
healing are the hot issue

00:11:59.510 --> 00:12:04.750 align:middle line:84%
in modern medicine, strongly
supported these days by NIH.

00:12:04.750 --> 00:12:06.640 align:middle line:84%
Now, as a physicist,
I would have

00:12:06.640 --> 00:12:10.890 align:middle line:84%
to say that physics does not
have a lot to say, presently,

00:12:10.890 --> 00:12:15.570 align:middle line:84%
about either inflowing
information from the distance

00:12:15.570 --> 00:12:19.170 align:middle line:84%
or from the future
or outflowing healing

00:12:19.170 --> 00:12:22.600 align:middle line:84%
intention across the
country and affecting,

00:12:22.600 --> 00:12:27.280 align:middle line:84%
beneficially, the physical
state of people in the hospital.

00:12:27.280 --> 00:12:31.690 align:middle line:84%
And what I observed in my
10 years sitting in the dark

00:12:31.690 --> 00:12:36.300 align:middle line:84%
with my eyes shut is that
between this interesting

00:12:36.300 --> 00:12:40.790 align:middle line:84%
condition of inflowing
information and outflowing

00:12:40.790 --> 00:12:45.720 align:middle line:84%
healing intention, by the
continuity that any physicist

00:12:45.720 --> 00:12:48.040 align:middle line:84%
would know, between the
inflow and the outflow,

00:12:48.040 --> 00:12:50.160 align:middle line:90%
there must be a quiet place.

00:12:50.160 --> 00:12:53.200 align:middle line:84%
In that quiet place
we have an opportunity

00:12:53.200 --> 00:12:57.670 align:middle line:84%
to experience the expanded
awareness that precipitates us

00:12:57.670 --> 00:13:05.440 align:middle line:84%
into an opportunity to reside
in love, to experience God,

00:13:05.440 --> 00:13:08.440 align:middle line:84%
to have the kind of
oceanic experiences

00:13:08.440 --> 00:13:10.230 align:middle line:90%
the mystics talk about.

00:13:10.230 --> 00:13:13.540 align:middle line:84%
And none of this, of course,
requires belief in anything.

00:13:13.540 --> 00:13:15.190 align:middle line:90%
None of this is dogma.

00:13:15.190 --> 00:13:21.150 align:middle line:84%
It's the path that all mystics
have had which says, basically,

00:13:21.150 --> 00:13:23.140 align:middle line:84%
if you will sit
down and be quiet,

00:13:23.140 --> 00:13:25.580 align:middle line:84%
you will have the
following experience.

00:13:25.580 --> 00:13:28.610 align:middle line:84%
It's like a lab report
that we do at Columbia

00:13:28.610 --> 00:13:31.860 align:middle line:84%
says that if you will stop
your mental chatter, if you'll

00:13:31.860 --> 00:13:36.360 align:middle line:84%
give up your judgment and
your fear and just be quiet,

00:13:36.360 --> 00:13:37.840 align:middle line:84%
we think that
you're going to have

00:13:37.840 --> 00:13:39.340 align:middle line:90%
some interesting experiences.

00:13:39.340 --> 00:13:42.360 align:middle line:84%
Why don't you go home,
do that for six weeks,

00:13:42.360 --> 00:13:45.270 align:middle line:84%
write it up, and let
us know what you found?

00:13:45.270 --> 00:13:46.740 align:middle line:84%
So it's a very
scientific approach.

00:13:46.740 --> 00:13:49.440 align:middle line:84%
There's no conflict
between spirituality

00:13:49.440 --> 00:13:52.920 align:middle line:90%
and a scientific frame of life.

00:13:52.920 --> 00:13:56.430 align:middle line:84%
And this experience
of expanded awareness,

00:13:56.430 --> 00:13:59.840 align:middle line:84%
this opportunity to
reside in a loving state,

00:13:59.840 --> 00:14:05.300 align:middle line:84%
is the reward for learning
to quit the ongoing chatter

00:14:05.300 --> 00:14:08.370 align:middle line:84%
and especially difficult for
a New Yorker like myself,

00:14:08.370 --> 00:14:11.220 align:middle line:84%
to give up some of my favorite
things like fear and judgment.

00:14:11.220 --> 00:14:13.770 align:middle line:90%


00:14:13.770 --> 00:14:16.040 align:middle line:84%
But in the end, it turns
out to be worthwhile.

00:14:16.040 --> 00:14:16.540 align:middle line:90%
Thank you.

00:14:16.540 --> 00:14:18.980 align:middle line:90%
[APPLAUSE]

00:14:18.980 --> 00:14:27.780 align:middle line:90%


00:14:27.780 --> 00:14:32.740 align:middle line:84%
>>All of us agree that
consciousness exists.

00:14:32.740 --> 00:14:36.240 align:middle line:84%
And my question is, is
consciousness a product

00:14:36.240 --> 00:14:40.100 align:middle line:84%
of the physiological
processes of the brain

00:14:40.100 --> 00:14:45.050 align:middle line:84%
or a fundamental
aspect of existence?

00:14:45.050 --> 00:14:48.350 align:middle line:84%
>>A slightly easier
way of phrasing it,

00:14:48.350 --> 00:14:50.280 align:middle line:84%
instead of talking
about consciousness,

00:14:50.280 --> 00:14:53.310 align:middle line:84%
which is somewhat
of a loose concept,

00:14:53.310 --> 00:14:55.290 align:middle line:90%
we might talk about awareness.

00:14:55.290 --> 00:14:59.010 align:middle line:84%
>>Well, awareness is good,
but Dr. Coker tonight,

00:14:59.010 --> 00:15:04.080 align:middle line:84%
was saying in physics that
he accepts consciousness,

00:15:04.080 --> 00:15:06.925 align:middle line:84%
that consciousness is part of
what's going on in physics.

00:15:06.925 --> 00:15:09.110 align:middle line:84%
Now are we talking about
the same thing here?

00:15:09.110 --> 00:15:11.780 align:middle line:84%
Are we talking about the
consciousness of the brain?

00:15:11.780 --> 00:15:17.140 align:middle line:84%
Or are we talking about it
as a fundamental situation

00:15:17.140 --> 00:15:18.260 align:middle line:90%
that exists?

00:15:18.260 --> 00:15:22.340 align:middle line:84%
>>Several years ago, I saw
in a bookstore the book

00:15:22.340 --> 00:15:23.460 align:middle line:90%
by Francis Crick.

00:15:23.460 --> 00:15:26.180 align:middle line:84%
It said "The
Astonishing Hypothesis."

00:15:26.180 --> 00:15:29.300 align:middle line:84%
Nobel Prize winning scientist
explains consciousness.

00:15:29.300 --> 00:15:32.230 align:middle line:84%
So I said, this is a
book I have to read.

00:15:32.230 --> 00:15:34.110 align:middle line:84%
So I bought the
book, open it up.

00:15:34.110 --> 00:15:36.830 align:middle line:84%
And at the beginning,
he says, well,

00:15:36.830 --> 00:15:41.000 align:middle line:84%
let's simplify it a little
to the problem of perception.

00:15:41.000 --> 00:15:43.600 align:middle line:84%
And then he gives
pages and pages

00:15:43.600 --> 00:15:46.870 align:middle line:84%
of experiments showing that
when we observe something,

00:15:46.870 --> 00:15:50.050 align:middle line:84%
there are changes happening in
the retina-- electric changes,

00:15:50.050 --> 00:15:51.820 align:middle line:90%
biochemical changes.

00:15:51.820 --> 00:15:54.790 align:middle line:84%
Then have many, many experiments
showing that things are

00:15:54.790 --> 00:15:57.390 align:middle line:90%
happening in the optical track.

00:15:57.390 --> 00:16:02.930 align:middle line:84%
Again, more electric currents,
more biochemical changes.

00:16:02.930 --> 00:16:07.700 align:middle line:84%
And then finally changes in
the suboccipital cortex- again,

00:16:07.700 --> 00:16:14.290 align:middle line:84%
electric potentials and
more biochemical changes.

00:16:14.290 --> 00:16:17.630 align:middle line:84%
And then he left it there,
where, obviously, that's

00:16:17.630 --> 00:16:19.020 align:middle line:90%
where the problem begins.

00:16:19.020 --> 00:16:23.450 align:middle line:84%
I mean, what is it that
is capable to create out

00:16:23.450 --> 00:16:28.900 align:middle line:84%
of these suboccipital
changes, electric potentials,

00:16:28.900 --> 00:16:35.750 align:middle line:84%
and biochemical changes, a
Technicolor sort of conscious

00:16:35.750 --> 00:16:38.530 align:middle line:84%
in our experience of
the object out there

00:16:38.530 --> 00:16:41.620 align:middle line:90%
that we are perceiving.

00:16:41.620 --> 00:16:43.160 align:middle line:84%
So I suddenly had
the feeling that I

00:16:43.160 --> 00:16:45.540 align:middle line:90%
was like in the Sufi story.

00:16:45.540 --> 00:16:48.635 align:middle line:84%
When there's a lamp
and under the lamp,

00:16:48.635 --> 00:16:51.080 align:middle line:84%
there's a guy sort of
looking for something.

00:16:51.080 --> 00:16:55.690 align:middle line:84%
Another guy comes and
says, what are you doing?

00:16:55.690 --> 00:16:57.610 align:middle line:90%
Says, well, I lost a key.

00:16:57.610 --> 00:16:58.960 align:middle line:90%
Says, can I help you?

00:16:58.960 --> 00:17:03.810 align:middle line:84%
So they both end up on their
knees looking for the key.

00:17:03.810 --> 00:17:07.200 align:middle line:84%
And then the newcomer says,
well, I can't see anything.

00:17:07.200 --> 00:17:08.449 align:middle line:90%
Are you sure you lost it here?

00:17:08.449 --> 00:17:10.670 align:middle line:90%
He says, no over there.

00:17:10.670 --> 00:17:11.710 align:middle line:90%
Says, over there?

00:17:11.710 --> 00:17:13.160 align:middle line:90%
Why are we looking here?

00:17:13.160 --> 00:17:15.619 align:middle line:84%
Says, we wouldn't have
a chance here, you know,

00:17:15.619 --> 00:17:16.770 align:middle line:90%
because there's light here.

00:17:16.770 --> 00:17:19.462 align:middle line:90%
Over there, there's dark.

00:17:19.462 --> 00:17:20.170 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:17:20.170 --> 00:17:24.109 align:middle line:84%
So in this book, he covered
a lot of experiments

00:17:24.109 --> 00:17:26.069 align:middle line:90%
of things that can be studied.

00:17:26.069 --> 00:17:29.020 align:middle line:84%
And then he left,
absolutely unanswered,

00:17:29.020 --> 00:17:31.750 align:middle line:84%
the question that really
cannot be answered.

00:17:31.750 --> 00:17:35.780 align:middle line:84%
I've never seen anybody in
any kind of scientific books

00:17:35.780 --> 00:17:39.640 align:middle line:84%
or articles even beginning
to tackle that question-- how

00:17:39.640 --> 00:17:44.240 align:middle line:84%
that gap between matter and
consciousness could be bridged.

00:17:44.240 --> 00:17:48.890 align:middle line:84%
How something that's inert,
that's reactive, that's dead

00:17:48.890 --> 00:17:51.990 align:middle line:84%
could create a sense
of self awareness,

00:17:51.990 --> 00:17:54.870 align:middle line:90%
a sense of consciousness.

00:17:54.870 --> 00:17:59.060 align:middle line:84%
So I myself came into the
work with nonordinary states

00:17:59.060 --> 00:18:02.550 align:middle line:84%
with a very firm conviction
that was kind of instilled

00:18:02.550 --> 00:18:04.070 align:middle line:90%
in me by my medical training.

00:18:04.070 --> 00:18:08.410 align:middle line:84%
That it's absolutely obvious
that somehow consciousness

00:18:08.410 --> 00:18:11.080 align:middle line:84%
emerges out of the complexity
of the neurophysiological

00:18:11.080 --> 00:18:15.960 align:middle line:84%
processes, until I became aware
of a category of experiences

00:18:15.960 --> 00:18:20.020 align:middle line:84%
that we call transpersonal
now-- experiences in which

00:18:20.020 --> 00:18:23.690 align:middle line:84%
in these nonordinary
states, we can

00:18:23.690 --> 00:18:26.530 align:middle line:84%
experience the dissolution
of our boundaries

00:18:26.530 --> 00:18:29.460 align:middle line:84%
and experience ourselves
as another person,

00:18:29.460 --> 00:18:31.850 align:middle line:84%
or experience a
group consciousness,

00:18:31.850 --> 00:18:35.910 align:middle line:84%
or experience extremely
authentic identification

00:18:35.910 --> 00:18:38.930 align:middle line:84%
with other life
forms from primates

00:18:38.930 --> 00:18:48.010 align:middle line:84%
all the way down to protozoan,
unicellular organisms.

00:18:48.010 --> 00:18:52.770 align:middle line:84%
Experiences in which we can
and go into archetypal domains.

00:18:52.770 --> 00:18:56.560 align:middle line:84%
We can experience and
encounter archetypal figures

00:18:56.560 --> 00:19:00.270 align:middle line:84%
from different cultures, from
mythologies that we have never

00:19:00.270 --> 00:19:03.855 align:middle line:84%
studied-- the Jungian idea of
the collective unconscious.

00:19:03.855 --> 00:19:06.710 align:middle line:90%


00:19:06.710 --> 00:19:09.720 align:middle line:84%
Now I'll just mention
one experience

00:19:09.720 --> 00:19:12.370 align:middle line:84%
that everybody will know
that obviously showing

00:19:12.370 --> 00:19:14.990 align:middle line:84%
that consciousness can do
things that the brain couldn't

00:19:14.990 --> 00:19:15.710 align:middle line:90%
possibly do.

00:19:15.710 --> 00:19:18.420 align:middle line:84%
At least, not the kind
of brain that we describe

00:19:18.420 --> 00:19:21.160 align:middle line:90%
in our university studies.

00:19:21.160 --> 00:19:27.270 align:middle line:84%
And that's the famous experience
that thanatologists see.

00:19:27.270 --> 00:19:29.880 align:middle line:90%
It's now absolutely obvious.

00:19:29.880 --> 00:19:33.390 align:middle line:84%
It has been confirmed many times
that it's possible for a person

00:19:33.390 --> 00:19:37.430 align:middle line:84%
to have an experience
of clinical death.

00:19:37.430 --> 00:19:40.500 align:middle line:84%
And as that person is
being resuscitated,

00:19:40.500 --> 00:19:42.570 align:middle line:84%
the subjective experience
is that consciousness

00:19:42.570 --> 00:19:45.970 align:middle line:84%
detaches from the
body and is freely

00:19:45.970 --> 00:19:49.430 align:middle line:84%
moving in the environment
and maintaining

00:19:49.430 --> 00:19:53.280 align:middle line:84%
the perception of the
environment without senses.

00:19:53.280 --> 00:19:56.990 align:middle line:84%
The person is lying in a
coma with the eyes closed.

00:19:56.990 --> 00:19:59.650 align:middle line:84%
And this embodied consciousness
can perceive the environment--

00:19:59.650 --> 00:20:01.385 align:middle line:90%
>>Flat EEG--

00:20:01.385 --> 00:20:04.110 align:middle line:90%
>>Flat EEG sometimes.

00:20:04.110 --> 00:20:08.020 align:middle line:84%
This can be observing, for
example, the whole situation

00:20:08.020 --> 00:20:09.650 align:middle line:90%
from the ceiling.

00:20:09.650 --> 00:20:14.440 align:middle line:84%
And then decides to check on
the situation and floats down

00:20:14.440 --> 00:20:19.760 align:middle line:84%
and checks the gauges on
the defibrillation machine.

00:20:19.760 --> 00:20:23.670 align:middle line:84%
And then decides to
go for a little walk.

00:20:23.670 --> 00:20:25.440 align:middle line:90%
Goes through the walls.

00:20:25.440 --> 00:20:29.272 align:middle line:84%
Check what's happening in
other parts of the building.

00:20:29.272 --> 00:20:30.730 align:middle line:84%
And then maybe
experience something

00:20:30.730 --> 00:20:35.660 align:middle line:84%
that's happening 200
or 2,000 miles away.

00:20:35.660 --> 00:20:39.840 align:middle line:84%
And then when the person
comes back to consciousness--

00:20:39.840 --> 00:20:42.860 align:middle line:84%
if there is a person who is
interested in this phenomenon

00:20:42.860 --> 00:20:46.130 align:middle line:84%
and gets the
accounts and checks,

00:20:46.130 --> 00:20:48.380 align:middle line:84%
the person finds out that
these things are really

00:20:48.380 --> 00:20:52.580 align:middle line:84%
happening-- all these locations
the disembodied consciousness

00:20:52.580 --> 00:20:56.430 align:middle line:84%
had the capacity
to see, to perceive

00:20:56.430 --> 00:20:59.440 align:middle line:90%
without the sensory organs.

00:20:59.440 --> 00:21:02.250 align:middle line:84%
There's now a book
by Ken Ring, probably

00:21:02.250 --> 00:21:05.130 align:middle line:84%
the most famous
thanatologist, which

00:21:05.130 --> 00:21:08.750 align:middle line:84%
is called "Mindsight" where
he describes his recent study

00:21:08.750 --> 00:21:11.800 align:middle line:84%
where people who are
congenitally blind

00:21:11.800 --> 00:21:16.520 align:middle line:84%
were able to see at
the time when they had

00:21:16.520 --> 00:21:19.570 align:middle line:84%
a near-death experience,
and their consciousness

00:21:19.570 --> 00:21:21.760 align:middle line:84%
was out of their
body, and then lost

00:21:21.760 --> 00:21:23.900 align:middle line:84%
the capacity to
see again when they

00:21:23.900 --> 00:21:26.870 align:middle line:90%
reconnected with their body.

00:21:26.870 --> 00:21:30.200 align:middle line:84%
And he is particularly
interested in studying

00:21:30.200 --> 00:21:33.400 align:middle line:84%
experiences that he calls
vertical out-of-body

00:21:33.400 --> 00:21:36.850 align:middle line:84%
experiences, where these
people not only see something,

00:21:36.850 --> 00:21:41.170 align:middle line:84%
but what they see is there
for other people in consensus

00:21:41.170 --> 00:21:43.400 align:middle line:90%
reality.

00:21:43.400 --> 00:21:47.840 align:middle line:84%
So to me, this is a paradigm
challenge if I ever saw one.

00:21:47.840 --> 00:21:50.040 align:middle line:84%
I don't know how
anybody could explain

00:21:50.040 --> 00:21:52.090 align:middle line:84%
it was the kind of
conceptual framework

00:21:52.090 --> 00:21:54.800 align:middle line:84%
that we are teaching
in our universities.

00:21:54.800 --> 00:21:56.100 align:middle line:90%
>>Thank you.

00:21:56.100 --> 00:21:59.140 align:middle line:84%
>>The question you're
asking is the very topic

00:21:59.140 --> 00:22:01.870 align:middle line:84%
that was in at least the French
editions of TIME magazine

00:22:01.870 --> 00:22:04.300 align:middle line:84%
last week, whether
or not consciousness

00:22:04.300 --> 00:22:08.210 align:middle line:84%
is an artifact of
physiology or whether or not

00:22:08.210 --> 00:22:17.040 align:middle line:84%
it's something that is around
us and has always existed.

00:22:17.040 --> 00:22:18.430 align:middle line:90%
So we're tossing out new ideas.

00:22:18.430 --> 00:22:20.930 align:middle line:84%
There's a growing
body of research

00:22:20.930 --> 00:22:25.254 align:middle line:84%
to suggest that consciousness,
for lack-- and the terms

00:22:25.254 --> 00:22:27.920 align:middle line:84%
and the semantics come into play
here because we haven't defined

00:22:27.920 --> 00:22:30.490 align:middle line:84%
any of these words-- but
suggest that consciousness

00:22:30.490 --> 00:22:34.410 align:middle line:84%
is the field of information,
the living body of information,

00:22:34.410 --> 00:22:38.490 align:middle line:84%
that surrounds
physical dimensions.

00:22:38.490 --> 00:22:42.020 align:middle line:90%


00:22:42.020 --> 00:22:44.080 align:middle line:84%
And there's a growing
body of evidence

00:22:44.080 --> 00:22:46.120 align:middle line:84%
to suggest-- let
me just ask you,

00:22:46.120 --> 00:22:48.710 align:middle line:84%
how many of you
in your textbooks

00:22:48.710 --> 00:22:53.750 align:middle line:84%
were taught that we remember
and hold memories in our brains?

00:22:53.750 --> 00:22:54.650 align:middle line:90%
How many of you?

00:22:54.650 --> 00:22:56.734 align:middle line:84%
Isn't that pretty much
what we've all been taught?

00:22:56.734 --> 00:22:58.191 align:middle line:84%
It was certainly
what I was taught.

00:22:58.191 --> 00:22:59.790 align:middle line:84%
There's a growing
body of research

00:22:59.790 --> 00:23:02.560 align:middle line:84%
that suggests that we may not
actually remember in our brains

00:23:02.560 --> 00:23:06.750 align:middle line:84%
the way we think we do--
that the neural circuits

00:23:06.750 --> 00:23:11.250 align:middle line:84%
in our brains actually
function as a very

00:23:11.250 --> 00:23:14.390 align:middle line:84%
specific form of
antenna that tune

00:23:14.390 --> 00:23:18.860 align:middle line:84%
to the fields of information
that surround and are held

00:23:18.860 --> 00:23:22.700 align:middle line:84%
in place, by some estimates,
in the magnetic fields

00:23:22.700 --> 00:23:25.610 align:middle line:84%
of our Earth, much the
way computer circuits

00:23:25.610 --> 00:23:30.730 align:middle line:84%
are held in place in magnetic
fields of memory and chips.

00:23:30.730 --> 00:23:32.470 align:middle line:84%
And if that turns
out to be true,

00:23:32.470 --> 00:23:35.620 align:middle line:84%
the implications to this
question, then, are vast.

00:23:35.620 --> 00:23:38.800 align:middle line:84%
It means that we simply
have the ability to tune

00:23:38.800 --> 00:23:43.880 align:middle line:84%
to the information in
creation and the ability

00:23:43.880 --> 00:23:47.600 align:middle line:84%
to change the way that we
tune into that information.

00:23:47.600 --> 00:23:49.730 align:middle line:84%
I had the opportunity a
few years ago-- Michio,

00:23:49.730 --> 00:23:53.380 align:middle line:84%
maybe you've seen
the thin sections

00:23:53.380 --> 00:23:56.475 align:middle line:84%
they made of Dr. Einstein's
brain after he died.

00:23:56.475 --> 00:24:00.060 align:middle line:84%
The University of
Kansas freeze dried

00:24:00.060 --> 00:24:01.930 align:middle line:84%
in thin section of
Albert Einstein's brain

00:24:01.930 --> 00:24:03.388 align:middle line:84%
because they wanted
to see what was

00:24:03.388 --> 00:24:06.541 align:middle line:84%
